Merge pull request #6 from yukawa/support_static_lib_for_win

Introduce ZINNIA_STATIC_LIBRARY for Windows

Introduce ZINNIA_STATIC_LIBRARY for Windows

Currently ZINNIA_DLL_EXTERN macro defined in zinnia.h can only be either
__declspec(dllexport) or __declspec(dllimport), which results in a
compile error for projects that want to use Zinnia as a static library.

With this CL, we can specify ZINNIA_STATIC_LIBRARY to build and use
Zinnia as a static library on Windows.

Merge pull request #5 from yukawa/remove_pyc

Remove zinnia.pyc.

Remove zinnia.pyc file.

zinnia.pyc is a byte code file, which we generally don't want to check
in into the source code repository.

Merge pull request #4 from yukawa/fix_make_pair_for_cxx11

Fix compile error of std::make_pair in C++11

Fix compile error of std::make_pair in C++11

std::make_pair is not designed to be used with explicit type
parameters.  In practice doing that can result in compile error
with Clang 3.4 on Ubuntu 14.04 when C++11 is enabled.

This CL removes explicit type parameters so that Zinnia can be
built even if C++11 is enabled.

Merge pull request #2 from yukawa/fix_win_unicode_build

Fix Windows build when UNICODE macro is specified.

Merge pull request #3 from yukawa/fix_msvc_build

Include <iterator> for VC++2010 and later

Fix Windows build when UNICODE macro is specified.

When UNICODE macro is specified, CreateFile is mapped to
CreateFileW rather than CreateFileA, which results in a
build error due to incompatible types.

We can support both cases by using CreateFileA explicitly.
